Man...did it snow.&nbsp; I'm glad it's the weekend <SPAN class=goog-spellcheck-word>cuz</SPAN> we aren't going anywhere.&nbsp; I think it's about 9 inches.&nbsp; That's not a HUGE amount but it's definitely significant.&nbsp; We just took the kids out to play in it.&nbsp; Wife is making them hot chocolate now while the cuddle up on the couch and <SPAN class=goog-spellcheck-word>watch</SPAN> Winnie the pooh.&nbsp; The best part is the memories they will have.&nbsp; OK...getting too mushy now.&nbsp; 

I'm trying to get another tattoo.&nbsp; Problem is Rick is busy.&nbsp; He's doing tattoos every weekend.&nbsp; I'm just hoping one day he'll call me up like last time and be like, "Hey, you ready for your tattoo."&nbsp; <SPAN class=goog-spellcheck-word>Cuz</SPAN> I really don't know when he'll be able to do it.&nbsp; And I certainly don't want to be a bother.&nbsp; I think I'm gonna try to cover up one I got now.&nbsp; It's really the only one I'm not happy with.&nbsp; It was flash for one thing (flash&nbsp;are the pictures hanging on the wall at the <SPAN class=goog-spellcheck-word>tatt</SPAN> studio).&nbsp; 

I better get going.&nbsp; It's almost lunch time.&nbsp; Later.

Hey.&nbsp; Went with Jon on one of our drives last night.&nbsp; We sometimes go driving off on some strange road just to see where we'd end up.&nbsp; It's fun.&nbsp; Wish we could do it tonight.&nbsp; Gotta work tomorrow though.&nbsp; Even though it's Memorial day.&nbsp; Oh well.&nbsp; No big.&nbsp; Saw X-men with him and Nick last night too.&nbsp; It was pritty good.&nbsp; If not a little depressing.&nbsp; It is after all supposed to be the last one.&nbsp; And we were just getting started too.&nbsp; Biggest let down of the entire series is of course no Gambit.&nbsp; And also that Sabertooth was only in the first one.&nbsp; That's f**king stupid if you ask me.&nbsp; Really f**king stupid.&nbsp; Not just a let down...it angers me.&nbsp; Actually pisses me off.&nbsp; I get pissed off enough in the real world I don't need that sh*t in the movies, too.&nbsp; Oh well.&nbsp; Nothing I can do about it I guess.&nbsp; 

**sigh**&nbsp;&nbsp; I wish I could go do something tonight.&nbsp; 

Anyway...later...

Lets see.&nbsp; Not much to report.&nbsp; Drove by the Balloon Glow (it's a derby thing) for my daughter yesterday.&nbsp; She was all excited.&nbsp; Didn't do much today...lawn work...grocery...that's about it.&nbsp; Hung wit Jon tonight.&nbsp; Went to Heine Bro's. coffee shop.&nbsp; And B-dubs.&nbsp; Saw his new home.&nbsp; He defiantly gots more room for his stuff.&nbsp; That's for sure.&nbsp; I don't like where it is.&nbsp; It's far off.&nbsp; Oh well.&nbsp; It was cool to just go hang out.&nbsp; Even though he was dead on his feet having run a marathon earlier.&nbsp; No...I mean that literally.&nbsp; The "Mini Marathon".&nbsp; It's a derby thing too.&nbsp; It's all derbied out here this week.&nbsp; 

Monday, all Hispanic, Latino, Mexican immigrants are having a boycott.&nbsp; None of them are supposed to work.&nbsp; Or buy anything.&nbsp; To teach us a lesson that they are so dire to our society.&nbsp; It's all in response to all the new proposals about making it so illegal immigrants are to be considered actual "criminals" hence forth and that a fence be erected along the boarder to keep them out.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here's how I feel about the so called boycott:

1. The illegal immigrants will be joined by LEGAL immigrants who support there "illegal brothers".&nbsp; Therefore the boycott is null and void because it wont be showing us what we'd be missing by having no "Illegal Immagrants".&nbsp; Cuz the LEGAL ones are doin' it too, see?
2.&nbsp; If your a guest you don't go ramming things down your hosts throat and acting all foolish about it.&nbsp; Especially if your an uninvited guest.&nbsp; Let's say you have people over and one guy you don't even know and didn't invite comes crashing in.&nbsp; You tell him to leave.&nbsp; All the sudden he's all like, "Hey, that aint right.&nbsp; That's it.&nbsp; Im not drinking any of your beer."&nbsp; A bit audacious of him, don't you think?
3.&nbsp; Sure, they won't be buying selling or working.&nbsp; But I bet they'll still be collecting they're government benifets.&nbsp; Let's see them not get those for a day.&nbsp;&nbsp; It'll all even out.&nbsp; 

Now don't get me wrong.&nbsp; Im all for LEGAL immagrants.&nbsp; That's what this country is about.&nbsp; But you gotta do it the right way.&nbsp; That's just all there is too it.&nbsp; It's hard for the others to come in here when the go about it the correct way.&nbsp; They've earned there stripes one could say.&nbsp; That's great.&nbsp; Good for them.&nbsp; Welcome.&nbsp; But just do it RIGHT.&nbsp; If you break ANY law, your breaking the law.&nbsp; Period.&nbsp; Oh and I DO NOT like them redoing the National Anthem in spanish.&nbsp; That's just plain not right.&nbsp; Integrate or evacuate.&nbsp; Like I said don't get me wrong.&nbsp; I am all for immagration.&nbsp; But this changing our song and boycotting crap has got to go.&nbsp; Or else they do.&nbsp;

Hiya.&nbsp; Been a bit.&nbsp; Whole family has been sick this past week.&nbsp; Stomache flu.&nbsp; I think we don't with it.&nbsp; I hope.&nbsp; That was some rough stuff, man.&nbsp; Rough.&nbsp; 

Anyhoo.&nbsp; Things is okay.&nbsp; Still rollin' round the airport in a truck for a living.&nbsp; I don't mind the job.&nbsp; It's nice when its a nice day and I actually get to be out seeing the sun, listing to tunes on MyPod, breeze hitting me in the face.&nbsp; Im gonna be goin' to school on the weekends.&nbsp; Gonna actaully make something of myself before it's too late.&nbsp; Don't know what yet though.&nbsp; 

Well.&nbsp; It's friday (havn't been happy 'bout that in a long time...now I get weekends off though...YAY) and my wifes almost home.&nbsp; Probably gonna go mow the lawn (yuck).&nbsp; Later.

Got a new posistion at work.&nbsp; Maintenance.&nbsp; Pays the same but it's full time.&nbsp; Although some of the work is more physical there is also more oppertunity to do nothing.&nbsp; Like when Im rolling around in the truck patroling the grounds im just sittin' in the truck listening to Coast to Coast am on my ipod.&nbsp; So there are deffinate perks.&nbsp; 

I doubt that it is mutual but I kinda miss workin' with Jon.&nbsp; He's third shift Im second (another reason I needed to take the job, the shift change).&nbsp; We used to hang out and talk and go get food and sometimes play psp n stuff.&nbsp; Course latley it's been rough there and we hadn't had a chance to do that anyway.&nbsp; I don't know...in the end it's for the best.&nbsp; 

Today was Melissa's birthday.&nbsp; She was off work but I doubt it very much if she had a good bithday.&nbsp; I failed again.&nbsp; Always have...always will.&nbsp; Well...it's late and I gotta go in pritty early tomorrow so I guess I better be off to bed.&nbsp; Besides, I hear thunder rolling in...and I don't like having my computer on during a thunderstorm.&nbsp; So Later.&nbsp; Damn...I hope I can get to sleep tonight...sigh...

23 degrees.&nbsp; 23 freakin' degrees.&nbsp; It's the 3rd day of SPRING and it's 23 cold ass degrees.&nbsp; Spring is supposed to be a time of warming.&nbsp; A time when new life begins to grow.&nbsp; The birds come home.&nbsp; The seedlings begin to push themselves up out of the thawing earth to begin life anew.&nbsp; 32 degrees is the temperature at which water freezes.&nbsp; That means that today, the 3rd day of spring, it is BELOW FREEZING.&nbsp; WTF??&nbsp; It gets better.&nbsp; It's 23...but with the wind...the windchill...get this...17 freakin' degrees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Spring has brought me a new plant for me to enjoy.&nbsp; Today, I saw growing just outside my bedroom window a new edition to my garden.&nbsp; An Ice Bush.&nbsp; Yes...a bush covered in freakin' ice.&nbsp; 

Enough of that.&nbsp; Today was okay...but tonight at worked sucked.&nbsp; Peeps are still actin' like jerks to me and not talkin' to me.&nbsp; Pissin' me off.&nbsp; Jon was supposed to find out why and call me but he didn't.&nbsp; Sucks...now I gotta try n go to sleep on it.&nbsp; 

I got the kids tomorrow so I get very little sleep so I gotta jet n get in as much as I can.&nbsp; Later.

It has been far to long since I have used this journal.&nbsp; I don't why I felt compelled to renew my interest now but it seems I have.&nbsp; No matter.&nbsp;&nbsp; 

To bring you up to date.&nbsp; My youngest child is 8 months old today.&nbsp; She is able to pull her self to a sitting posistion from a laying posistion and she rocks back and forth in preperation for the next milestone in her life; crawling.&nbsp; She actually scoots herself forward in a "near-crawl" manner, however she has yet to actually crawl.&nbsp; It will be soon.&nbsp; No rush is necessary as some infants do things at different times.&nbsp; My oldest (who is a wise 4 year old) is quite smart for her age in many respects and she didn't begin walking until after the one year mark.&nbsp; As long as the milestones take place withen a certin respectable limit it really doesn't matter when or how early or late they do these things.&nbsp; But I digress.&nbsp; I Put these parts in mostly for myself so for whomever else may read, sorry if I go on too much.

I am still employed at the airport with Jon.&nbsp; I don't think I will be for long though.&nbsp; I'm getting pritty sick of it there.&nbsp; As I am sure they are getting sick of me.&nbsp; Evident in the fact that most of the employes will often not speak to me and will infact go out of there way make sure I know they are not speaking to me.&nbsp; It all gets old.&nbsp; I care not, however.&nbsp; I am only there for one thing, really; Money.&nbsp; I'm quite sure Jon would be happy to see me leave there also.&nbsp; I am sure he is tired of working with me.&nbsp; Perhaps it's because I bitch too much (which I admit I do at times) or perhaps he is just tired of having to see me every night.&nbsp; And then hang out at times out side of work.&nbsp; I know not.&nbsp; I care not.&nbsp; I don't want to lose a friend because of a job I don't even really like.&nbsp; It isn't as if I can advance at all at this place.&nbsp; I have been thinking of going back to the world of dog grooming.&nbsp; I miss working with animals.&nbsp; People are sometimes jerks and you begin hating working with them.&nbsp; At least when a dog is a jerk you can justify it by remembering that a dogs mental and emotional capiablities are about equal to that of a 4 year old.&nbsp; That at least makes it easier to understand them.&nbsp; I would miss working with Jon, though.&nbsp; Although as I said already I don't think that would be a mutual feeling.&nbsp; 

That is about all I have to write about at this time.&nbsp; Not much else is going on.&nbsp; My grandfather is doing much better.&nbsp; My sister is doing ok.&nbsp; I havn't talked with my dad in like 2 months.&nbsp; His fault, I called him and he never called back.&nbsp; Ball is in his court.&nbsp; That is all.&nbsp; Sorry for this long winded self&nbsp; deprecating rant.&nbsp; Good night.<!--StartFragment -->
